static.report.forecastErrorMonthlyFormul: The WAPE formula is using the previous 3-12 months of data depending on the selection in the ‘Time Window’ dropdown.
A month labeled `Total actual consumption for last 6 months = 0` means that the summation of the actual consumption for the usable months in the selected time window was 0.

A month labeled `No months in this period contain both forecast and actual consumption` means that there are no months in the selected time window that have both actual and forecast records in the same month.
The forecast error can go above 100% and the higher the %, the worse the forecast is.

Only months that have both a forecast and an actual consumption record are included in the forecast error calculation. The column to the right of the forecast error details how many months were included in that calculation.
A planning unit labeled ` Total actual consumption for last 6 months = 0` means that the summation of the actual consumption for the usable months in the selected time window was 0.

A planning unit labeled ` No months in this period contain both forecast and actual consumption ` means that there are no months in the selected time window that have both actual and forecast records in the same month.

static.supplyPlanFormula.endingBalance1: Ending balance = Opening balance + Adjustments + Shipments in account - Consumptions - Expired stock
static.supplyPlanFormula.amcNote: * Consider only non zero values. Also current month is included in the months in future for AMC
static.supplyPlanFormula.amcEx1: Months in past = 3(Based on program planning unit)
static.supplyPlanFormula.amcEx2: Months in future = 3(Based on program planning unit)
static.supplyPlanFormula.amcEx10: AMC =  Consumption in No. of MONTHS_IN_PAST + Consumption in No. of MONTHS_IN_FUTURE/ number of months
static.supplyPlanFormula.minStockEx5: Min= AMC * MAX (MIN MONTH OF STOCK,Min MoS Guardrail)
static.supplyPlanFormula.maxStockEx6: Max = AMC * MIN ([ MAX(MIN MONTH OF STOCK ,Min MoS Guardrail) + REORDER FREQUENCY ] ,Max MoS Guardrail)
static.supplyPlanFormula.minMonthOfStock: Min= MAX (MIN MONTH OF STOCK,Min MoS Guardrail)
static.supplyPlanFormula.maxMonthOfStock: Max = MIN ( [ MAX(MIN MONTH OF STOCK ,3) + REORDER FREQUENCY ] ,Min MoS Guardrail )
static.supplyPlanFormula.suggestedOrderQ: Suggested Order Qty = (Max Stock - Ending balance)
static.supplyPlanFormula.monthsOfStockEx: Months Of Stock = Ending Balance / AMC
static.supplyPlanFormula.costOfInventory: Note: If `Include planned shipment` is `yes` - Planned, Submitted, Approved, Shipped, Arrived, Received, On Hold statuses are all included in the projected inventory. If `no`, all above statuses are included except Planned.
